m,\, k
\mbox{Evaluate}\qquad \lim_{n \to \infty}\left\{% \left[\sum_{r = 1}^{k}{\left(n + r\right)^{m} \over n^{m - 1}}\right] -kn \right\} 
\lim_{n \to \infty} (\frac{(\sum_{r=1}^{k}(n+r)^m)-kn^m}{n^{m-1}})= \lim_{n\to \infty}(\frac{\sum_{n=1}^{k}((n+r)^m-n^m)}{n^{m-1}})=\lim_{n\to \infty}\frac{\sum_{r=1}^{k}r((n+r)^{m-1}+\cdots + n^{m-1})}{n^{m-1}}=\lim_{n\to \infty}\sum_{r=1}^{k}r((1+\frac{r}{n})^{m-1}+(1+\frac{r}{n})^{m-2}+\cdots +(1+\frac{r}{n})+1)=\sum_{r=1}^{k} \frac{r((1+\frac{r}{n})^m)-1)}{(1+\frac{r}{n})-1}=\lim_{n \to \infty}\sum_{r=1}^{k}n((1+\frac{r}{n})^m-1)
rm
\frac{mk(k+1)}{2}
